SIMPLE: ocean
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ocean
<hw>O"cean</hw> <pr>(⟦omac⟧"sh⟦ait⟧n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>oc⟦eacute⟧an</ets>, L. <ets>oceanus</ets>, Gr. <grk>'wkeano`s</grk>
ocean, in Homer, the great river supposed to encompass the earth.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>The whole body of salt water which covers more than
three fifths of the surface of the globe; -- called also the
<altname>sea</altname>, or <altname>great sea</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Like the odor of brine from the <qex>ocean</qex>⟦br⟧
<qex>Comes the thought of other years</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Longfellow.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One of the large bodies of water into which the
great ocean is regarded as divided, as the Atlantic, Pacific, Indian,
Arctic and Antarctic <ex>oceans</ex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>An immense expanse; any vast space or quantity
without apparent limits; <as>as, the boundless <ex>ocean</ex> of
eternity; an <ex>ocean</ex> of affairs.</as></def>
<rj><au>Locke.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>You're gonna need an <qex>ocean</qex>⟦br⟧
Of calamine lotion.</q> <rj><qau>Lieber & Stoller (Poison Ivy: song
lyrics, 1994)</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ocean</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Ocean
<hw>O"cean</hw> <pr>(⟦omac⟧"sh⟦ait⟧n)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Of or
pertaining to the main or great sea; <as>as, the <ex>ocean</ex> waves;
an <ex>ocean</ex> stream.</as></def> <rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

